Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add chops; cook 5 min. on each side or until browned on both sides. Add peppers, pineapple with its juice, broth, dressing and garlic powder; mix well. Bring to boil. Stir in rice; cover. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 5 min. or until chops are cooked through (160 degrees F.) Remove from heat; let stand 5 min.